-- China Says Japan in No Position to Criticize Yuan Policy After Surpluses
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-15T02:48:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/china-says-japan-in-no-position-to-criticize-yuan-policy-after-surpluses.html
Japan is in no position to criticize
China on the value of the yuan, Yao Jian, spokesman for China’s
Ministry of Commerce, said at a briefing in Beijing today.  Japan has run trade surpluses with China for eight years
from 2003 to 2010 and benefited “hugely” from bilateral trade,
Yao said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
